# Introduction to Python

Python is a high-level, interpreted programming language created by Guido van Rossum and first released in 1991.

It is designed to be simple, readable, and easy to learn, which makes it one of the most popular programming languages in the world.

## Why Python is Popular

Python is widely used because of its simplicity and powerful features:

- Easy to learn and beginner-friendly
- Clean and readable syntax
- Large global community
- Huge number of libraries and frameworks
- Works on multiple operating systems (Windows, Linux, macOS)

## Common Uses of Python

Python is used in many fields of technology, including:

- Web development
- Data science and machine learning
- Artificial intelligence
- Automation and scripting
- Desktop application development
- Cybersecurity tools

